\subsection{Testing Proportionality Assumption}

Cox \emph{proportional} rest on the assumption that hazard rates are proportional to time dynamics\footnote{\citet{Box-Steffensmeier2004}.}. Non-proportional hazard model are becoming an increasing problem across all subfields in political science\footnote{\citet{Licht2011}.}. In this section, we test whether this assumption holds. Non-significant p-values indicate that the proportionality assumption holds. Also, \autoref{fig:coxassump} shows how the spline fitted lines (i.e., the regression coefficients of the main model) are almost constant across time, confirming that the hazard rates are, in fact, \emph{proportional}.

